thread.title: The most BOGAN baby names of 2017
thread.title_full: The most BOGAN baby names of 2017 | Daily Mail Online

author: Lauren Ingram For Daily Mail Australia
title: The most BOGAN baby names of 2017

organizations.name: vegas nicoachus harleen braelyn jack daniel nashayleah

text:
When it comes to so called 'bogan' baby names, Australian parents have come a long way from giving their kids simple monikers like Shazza and Dazza.
Instead they're opting for more unusual names - like Allure, Vegas and Chayce.
Now author Sabrina Rogers-Anderson has now collected some of the best names in a new book, The Little Book of Bogan Baby Names .
My name is: The most bogan baby names have been revealed by expert Sabrina Rogers- Anderson
Ms Rogers-Anderson, who is a baby name expert, decided to collect more than 200 bogan names, as well as their meaning.
She included names like J'Zayden, a combination of favourites Jayden and Zaiden.
'Most readers have taken my bogan musings as they were intended – a good-natured laugh,' the author wrote about her work.
'We all have a bit of bogan in us that needs to be celebrated. Truth be told, I can’t help but like some of these names just a little bit.'
Unique: Many names have unusal spellings, such as Tahmykkha or Kymberleigh (stock image)
UNIQUE BOGAN BABY NAMES J'Zayden
Vegas
Nicoachus
Harleen
Braelyn
Jack Daniel
Nashayleah
Rebel
Wynter
Other popular bogan names included in her book are Nicomachus, Harleen and Braelyn.
While some of the names may be entirely new, there are some themes that emerge.
It appears that many of the names are often variations of more traditional names, but with different spelling and pronunciation.
The name Tamika, for example, has alternate spellings of Tahmykkha, Tameekah, Tameka-Jane, and Tammika.
Using names for places or things as a baby name is also popular, for example Vegas, Sierra-Leonie, Rocket, Khe Sanh and Narnia.
Inspiration: Some of the names were inspired by products, like Jack Daniel or Prada
Long names with excess letters are also common, like Alycesaundra, Torianna-Sharisse, Kymberleigh, Jhamasyn and Mackennziee.
A number of these examples are showcased on popular blog Things Bogans Like , which has an ongoing list of bogan baby names.
Product names are also popular with Jack Daniel, Diesel, Ricca-Donna, Prada and Jaguar making the blog's list of recorded names.
